cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the conversion of proofs from one logic system (HOL Light) to another (Metamath).
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the automation efforts in HOL Light and the embedding of HOL formalization into the Metamath library.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of automation in the proof conversion process.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possibility as the paper deals with the development of a software tool for proof conversion.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper discusses the algorithm used for the proof conversion process.
